@NODE "Intro"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Introduction
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    WarpSDL.library is a new shared library for future games/applications.
    It has its own custom command set, while at the same time supporting
    standard SDL commands, for easy porting. It is written entirely from
    scratch.

    The main reason for me writing this in the first place was to port
    ScummVM to AmigaOS without having to suffer from the speed-penalty that
    the normal SDL gives.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Reqs"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Requirements
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * AmigaOS 3.0+.

    * MC68020+ (or compatible).

    * Some fast-memory.

    * CyberGraphics V41+ (or compatible) required
      for 15bit+ displays and window-mode support.

    * 040/060 for AGA support.

    * AHI v4+ if you want sound.

    * psxport.device for psx-pad support.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Feat"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Features
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * AGA support in 8bit mode.
    
    * Window-mode on 15bit+ displays.
    
    * Full-screen support.

    * AHI support for sound.

    * Thread/subtask support.

    * PPC (WarpOS) support.

    * Supports joysticks, cd32pads and psxpads.

    * Supports CD audio.

    * +More.

    ------------------------------------------------------------------------

    @{b}The library inlcudes the following functions so far:@{ub}

    @{u}Added in 0.1:@{uu}
    WarpSDL_AllocMemory()           WarpSDL_FreeMemory()
    WarpSDL_Error()                 WarpSDL_GetError()
    WarpSDL_Init()                  WarpSDL_DeInit()
    WarpSDL_SetDisplay()            WarpSDL_CloseDisplay()
    WarpSDL_LockDisplay()           WarpSDL_UnLockDisplay()
    WarpSDL_SetColours()            WarpSDL_SetCursor()
    WarpSDL_ChangeTitle()           WarpSDL_UpdateArea()
    WarpSDL_UpdateAreas()           WarpSDL_FillArea()
    WarpSDL_BlitDisplay()           WarpSDL_DoTimeEvent()
    WarpSDL_GetEvent()              WarpSDL_CreateSubTask()
    WarpSDL_RemoveSubTask()         WarpSDL_OpenAudio()
    WarpSDL_CloseAudio()
    SDL_GetError()                  SDL_Init()
    SDL_Quit()                      SDL_SetVideoMode()
    SDL_LockSurface()               SDL_UnlockSurface()
    SDL_SetColors()                 SDL_ShowCursor()
    SDL_WM_SetCaption()             SDL_UpdateRect()
    SDL_UpdateRects()               SDL_FillRect()
    SDL_UpperBlit()                 SDL_GetTicks()
    SDL_Delay()                     SDL_PollEvent()
    SDL_CreateThread()              SDL_KillThread()
    SDL_OpenAudio()                 SDL_CloseAudio()

    @{u}Added in 0.2:@{uu}
    WarpSDL_SetNicePri()

    @{u}Added in 0.4:@{uu}
    WarpSDL_VirtualDisplay()        WarpSDL_MapRGB()
    WarpSDL_GetRGB()                WarpSDL_ToggleDisplayMode()
    WarpSDL_CountJoysticks()        WarpSDL_OpenJoystick()
    WarpSDL_OpenCD()                WarpSDL_CloseCD()
    WarpSDL_GetCDState()            WarpSDL_PlayCD()
    WarpSDL_StopCD()                WarpSDL_RemoveTimer()
    WarpSDL_AddTimer()
    SDL_CreateRGBSurface()          SDL_CreateRGBSurfaceFrom()
    SDL_MapRGB()                    SDL_MapRGBA()
    SDL_GetRGB()                    SDL_GetRGBA()
    SDL_PauseAudio()                SDL_WM_GetCaption()
    SDL_WM_SetIcon()                SDL_WM_ToggleFullScreen()
    SDL_InitSubSystem()             SDL_QuitSubSystem()
    SDL_NumJoysticks()              SDL_JoystickOpen()
    SDL_CDOpen()                    SDL_CDClose()
    SDL_CDStatus()                  SDL_CDPlayTracks()
    SDL_CDStop()                    SDL_RemoveTimer()
    SDL_SetTimer()                  SDL_AddTimer()

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 0.4                                                               (2002-10-24)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Added support for timed events.

    * Added support for audio cd's using direct-scsi. Also added the
      env-var(s) DEF_CDX_NAME to control the behaviour.

    * Preliminary support for joysticks, cd32pads & psxpads (psxport.device).

    * Extended the SDL commands-set and WarpSDL command-set, see @{"Features" link Feat}.

    * Smarter subtask-signalling implemented.

    * Depth and close gadgets added to wb-window displays.

    * Preliminary datatypes support added.

    * There was a memory leak when using 15bit+ displays, fixed.

    * More misc stuff related to 15bit+ displays fixed.

    * Implemented pixel-mapping.

    * Double buffering can now be forced on AGA screens, even if the
      application uses single-buffering... (As it looks crap
      otherwise... ;) Use the @{"DEF_FORCEDBUFFAGA" link Env} env-var to enable this.

    * Many more fixes and improvements.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 0.3                                                               (2002-02-22)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Reworked some bits and split up the code into more functions.

    * Fixed two OS related issues reported by PatchWorks.

    * Fixed a tiny memory leak.

    * Subtask signaling tweaked and modified to work better.

    * Priotities are now set correctly for WarpOS mirror-subtasks also.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 0.2r2                                                             (2002-02-18)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Added a fixed installation-script, as the one in the previous release
      only set the ENV variables in ENV: and not ENVARC:.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 0.2                                                               (2002-02-17)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * Added PPC support. (Still alot of context switches, will be minimized
      in the next couple of versions.)

    * Added support window-mode.

    * Added support for AGA using a custom C2P routine. (o4o/o6o)

    * Added the ability to control priorities of the main task and
      subtask(s) by using the env variables DEF_MOTHERTASK_PRI and
      DEF_SUBTASK_PRI. (Can be overriden by the application, but is used
      if it doesnt set a custom priority. And no application should,
      unless its an absolute must.)

    * The audio sub-task is no longer killed, but signaled before so it
      exits on its own.

    * Fixed some tiny bugs found in the library :).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 0.1                                                               (2002-02-09)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    * First alpha-beta-alpha-gamma release ;).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "FAQ"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Frequently asked questions
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    @{b}Q: Heeeeeeelp! Many WarpSDL applications crash!@{ub}     
    A: This is mostly stack related, as unix applications often use alot of
       stack. (I recommend installing StackAttack, or to just raise the
       stack before runing a WarpSDL application. If this doesnt solve it,
       install a ramlib patch. If it still doesnt work, @{"email me" link Author}! ;)

    @{b}Q: Why doesn't CD-Audio work!@{ub}     
    A: See the @{"bugs" link Bugs} section.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Installation
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    There is an easy way... Use the included installer ... ;)

    And there is a "hard" way... Move "warpsdl.library" into LIBS: and set
    the @{"ENV variables" link Env} you prefer by hand in ENV:/ENVARC:.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Env"

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Env variables
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    The env variables should reside in (ENV:/ENVARC:)warpsdl/, theese are the
    ones that can be set so far, and what they do:

    @{b}DEF_MOTHERTASK_PRI@{ub}     DEFAULT: 0.
    Sets the default priority of the main/mothertask, unless it overrides it,
    that priority will be used. Setting this env-variable higher than
    DEF_SUBTASK_PRI can result in sound that 'cuts' (if cpu consumption is at
    max).

    @{b}DEF_SUBTASK_PRI@{ub}        DEFAULT: 5.
    Sets the default priority of the subtask(s), unless they override it,
    that priority will be used. Setting this env-variable higher than
    DEF_MOTHERTASK_PRI can result in the game runing slower (if cpu
    consumption is at max), as the maintask won't get all the cpu power it
    might need."

    On PPC the priority values are translated into NICE values by subtracting
    the priority with (priority*2) and then dividing it with 5. So setting
    the priority to 5, will give you a PPC task that has the nicevalue -1.
    Setting it to 100-128 will give you a PPC task with the nicevalue -20,
    and so on.

    @{b}DEF_CDX_NAME@{ub}           DEFAULT: None.
    Used to configure and show warpsdl where your CD drives are. X is a value
    between 0 and 15. DEF_CD0_NAME is the primary CD drive and DEF_CD1_NAME
    is the secondary drive, and so on...

    Most often, applications use the primary drive, so setting DEF_CD0_NAME
    to "CD4:" will tell warpsdl applications to use CD4: as the primary
    CD drive.

    If you don't set DEF_CD0_NAME you tell warpsdl applications that you don't
    have a primary drive.

    @{b}DEF_FORCEDBUFFAGA@{ub}       DEFAULT: 0 (Off).
    Use this to force WarpSDL to use doublebuffering on AGA screens even
    if the application is made for single-buffering. This is done by storing
    the updated buffer in a "scratchbuffer"... This scratchbuffer is later
    applied to the old frame... Letting the application use the doublebuffered
    screen as a single-buffered one. :)... This can cause a slowdown when
    full-screen updates occur.

@ENDNODE

